60th Birthday of WPK Observed in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 25 (KCNA) -- Meetings were held at the head offices of the Communist Party Marxist-Leninist (R) in Sweden, the Communist Party of Malta and the Bulgarian Communist Party in the period from Oct. 7 to 14 to mark the 60th birthday of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 On display in the venues of the meetings were famous works of President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il and photos showing their undying exploits and books introducing the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Eric Andersson, international secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party Marxist-Leninist (R) in Sweden, said that the WPK founded by Kim Il Sung has guided the revolution and construction along a straight way of victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 John Zammit, secretary general of the Malta-Korea Friendship Association, said that the DPRK faced the worst adversity due to the frantic political and military pressure of the U.S.-led imperialist allied forces and their economic sanctions and severe natural calamities. But it held aloft the banner of building a great prosperous powerful nation, overcoming all sorts of trials and difficulties, and demonstrated its national power to the world by launching a satellite and declaring its possession of nukes, he noted, adding: This is the fruition of the wise leadership of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers including Lyudmil Kostantinov, chief of the Bulgarian Group for the Study of the Juche Idea, underscored the fact that the WPK has advanced along a straight path of victory without committing even a single mistake or undergoing any twist and turn in the way of implementing its line for the last 60 years because it has solved all problems independently and creatively, invariably guided by the Juche idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of meetings the participants watched Korean films "'Ever-Victorious Workers' Party of Korea', Grand Gymnastic and Artistic Performance for Celebrating the 55th Anniversary of the WPK" and "The Concrete Wall, Symbol of National Division." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, photo exhibitions and film shows took place in Indonesia, Malaysia, Thailand, Singapore and India in the period from Oct. 2 to 11.

Rodong Sinmun on Scenario for War of Aggression 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 25 (KCNA) -- The south Korean military authorities are seeking to punish a lawmaker of an opposition party on charges of disclosing such military secret as the "OPLAN 5027-04", a scenario of a preemptive nuclear attack on the north. Commenting on their action, Rodong Sinmun today denounces it as sympathy and instigation of the war frenzy of the bellicose forces at home and abroad.
 The commentary goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With the dangerous war scenario opened to the public the criminal plot of the U.S. and the south Korean bellicose elements for a war of aggression against the north has been brought to light again. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is now massively introducing latest war equipment into south Korea and stepping up the strategic relocation of its armed forces there under the pretext of bolstering their combat power and relocation. This indicates that its scenarios to invade and seize the north are being put into practice.
 The scheme of the south Korean authorities to harm the fellow countrymen by joining the foreign forces in their war moves is contrary to the desire of the nation and the trend of the times and an anti-national, anti-peace and anachronistic action for a war in the Korean Peninsula.

Japanese Reactionaries' Anti-DPRK, Anti-Chongryon Campaign under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 25 (KCNA) -- The Tokyo High Court held the second trial of the former financial director of the Central Standing Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) on Oct. 6 at which it sentenced him to six years in prison. He was arrested and prosecuted by the Japan investigation authorities on an absurd charge. In its wake the public security department of the Tokyo Metropolitan Police Agency searched for no reason several institutions related to Chongryon including the office of the Association of Korean Scientists and Technologists in Japan in the Korean Press Hall and the Kim Man Yu Scientific Promotion Society in Nishiarai Hospital in Tokyo.
 Rodong Sinmun Tuesday in a signed commentary carried in this regard observes: This rowdyism of crackdown on Chongryon is a revelation of the Japanese reactionaries' extremely hostile policy towards the DPRK and a blatant infringement upon its sovereignty. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries' evermore intensified anti-Chongryon and anti-DPRK campaign is aimed at slandering and hurting Chongryon, impairing the dignity and prestige of the DPRK and inciting bitterness towards Chongryon and the DPRK among the Japanese in a bid to create social atmosphere favorable for the revival of militarism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries should bear in mind that no matter how desperate they may become in their rackets against Chongryon and the DPRK they can never damage the dignity of Chongryon and the DPRK. The Japanese authorities should clearly understand that their campaign against Chongryon and the DPRK will adversely affect the DPRK-Japan relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries should immediately stop the suppression of Chongryon and apologize for their crimes against the DPRK and Chongryon.

Anniversary of Famous Work of Kim Jong Il Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 25 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today dedicates a signed article to the 15th anniversary of the publication of the famous work of leader Kim Jong Il "On Having a Correct Viewpoint and Understanding of the Juche Philosophy."
 The work published on Oct. 25, Juche 79 (1990) clarifies the idea that the Juche philosophy is a man-centered unique idea evolved and systematized with peculiar principles different from the preceding philosophies, the  essential character of man, the issue of understanding a social being and the issue of co-relation among the three forms of transformation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work serves as important guidelines for fully ensuring the purity of the Juche philosophy, the revolutionary and political philosophy of the Workers' Party of Korea, and as an inspiring banner that instilled into the Korean people the conviction of the advantages and greatness of the Juche idea, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ideas and theories set out in the work serve as an immortal militant banner as it imbues the Korean people and other progressives of the world with the steadfast Juche-oriented revolutionary outlook on the world and inspires them to wage a dynamic struggle for the victory of the cause of socialism. 
 It is the exploit Kim Jong Il performed in the development of the Juche philosophy that he scientifically proved the originality and validity of the Juche philosophy and put the position of the Juche idea on the highest level. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His another undying exploit is that he clarified the Juche philosophy is a man-centered new philosophical idea fundamentally different from the preceding philosophy of the working class and made it serve as a powerful theoretical and practical weapon truly conducive to revolutionary practice. 
 It is high pride and honor for the Workers' Party of Korea and the Korean people to have such a great revolutionary and political philosophy as the Juche philosophy, the article concludes.

Withdrawal of U.S. Troops from South Korea Urged
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 25 (KCNA) -- In order to establish national sovereignty throughout Korea and achieve the cause of national reunification and prosperity, all Koreans should struggle to have the foreign military bases dismantled and occupation forces withdrawn from south Korea. Rodong Sinmun Tuesday notes this in a signed article. It goes on:
 The reality proves that it is impossible to achieve national reunification, the true sovereignty of the country and national prosperity unless an end is put to the U. S. imperialists' policy of occupation of south Korea and their moves to provoke a new war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists chiefly responsible for the partition of the Korean Peninsula into two have built high political and physical barriers in a bid to block the Korean nation's development, prosperity, peace and independent reunification. It is due to the U.S. imperialists that the Korean nation with a history spanning 5,000 years still remains divided into the north and the south and has not yet achieved uniform development and prosperity in all fields of economy and social life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A tense situation always prevails in Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is impossible to realize the people's desire for uniform development and prosperity wherever peace is disturbed and a tense situation persists. 
 The June 15 era is the era of independent reunification in which the Koreans are paving the way for independent reunification through national reconciliation and unity. The Koreans are called upon to put a period to the U.S. policy of occupation of south Korea and drive the U.S. troops out of it in order to win back the sovereignty dearer than their life and soul and build a strong and prosperous reunified country to demonstrate the honor of the nation to the world, the article concludes.

Anniversary of CPV's Entry into Korean Front Observed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 25 (KCNA) -- Pyongyang-based papers today editorially observe the 55th anniversary of the entry of the Chinese People's Volunteers into the Korean front. 
 Rodong Sinmun says the servicepersons of the People's Army and people of the DPRK send militant salute to the fraternal servicepersons of the Chinese People's Liberation Army and people of China and pay high tribute to the CPV martyrs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their entry into the Korean front provided an opportunity to deepen the blood-sealed ties of militant fraternity and friendship between the two peoples, it notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The history of the DPRK-China friendship has steadily advanced along the track of its development. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This traditional friendship has reached a higher stage under the deep care of the top leaders of the two countries. In recent years leader Kim Jong Il visited China three times, bringing this friendship into fuller bloom. The DPRK visit by President Hu Jintao expected soon will mark an important occasion in boosting the bilateral friendship. In this century this friendship is growing stronger with a bright prospect in conformity with the desires and interests of the two peoples. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Chinese people have made great successes by making energetic endeavors to turn their country into a modern socialist country, holding fast to the important thought of "the three represents" under the correct leadership of the Communist Party of China headed by Hu Jintao. 
 They are radically changing the appearance of their country with their own energies and technology and through their creative efforts and making a dynamic advance towards a higher goal. A new turning phase is now being brought about in the just struggle of the Chinese people to reunify the whole country on the principle of "one country, two systems". The policy of the Chinese party and government for peace and development and cooperation relations is commanding support and sympathy of the world and China's prestige and voice are rising in the international arena day by day. 
 Everything is now going on well in China. The DPRK sincerely rejoices over this success as over its own. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today the two peoples enjoy the best time in the history of DPRK-China friendship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the steadfast stand of the DPRK to steadily boost the friendship generation after generation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The history of traditional DPRK-China friendship will make more dynamic progress in the future thanks to the concerted efforts of the parties, governments and peoples of the two countries.

Minju Joson on Japan's Bid for Permanent Seat of UN Security Council
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 25 (KCNA) -- Japan is resorting to all sorts of disgraceful conducts in an effort to take a permanent seat of the UN Security Council.
 Commenting on this, Minju Joson Tuesday says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A few days ago, a delegate of Japan, speaking at a UN General Assembly session, clamored that the qualification for a permanent seat of the UN Security Council should be appraised by the contribution of a relevant member nation to the international community. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's foolish assertion can never be overlooked as it is an intolerable mockery and insult to the UN and the international community.
 Japan should know that it is a wild dream for it to make a bid for a permanent seat of the UN Security Council with such a wrong stand.
 All the countries that want to have such a seat cannot have it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If Japan truly wants to make a responsible contribution to the UN, it should sincerely repent of its past crimes and clear off them, before ridiculously shaking a moneybag. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It should refrain from foolish act of inviting international isolation and shame and do what it should do.

Wreaths Laid before Friendship Tower
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 25 (KCNA) -- Wreaths were laid before the Friendship Tower Tuesday on the occasion of the 55th anniversary of the entry of the Chinese People's Volunteers into the Korean front.
 Present at the wreath-laying ceremony were Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, and other officials concerned and working people in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Amidst the playing of the wreath-laying music a wreath was placed before the tower in the joint name of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly and the DPRK Cabinet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Wreaths were laid before the tower in the name of the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces, the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, the Ministry of People's Security, the Ministry of Foreign Trade and the Ministry of Culture, a wreath in the joint name of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries and the Central Committee of the Korea-China Friendship Association and a wreath in the joint name of the Pyongyang City Committee of the WPK and the Pyongyang City People's Committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Working people in the city placed bouquets before the Friendship Tower. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Participants observed a moment's silence in memory of the martyrs of the Chinese People's Volunteers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also laid before the martyrs cemetery of the CPV in Hyongjesan District, Pyongyang, were a wreath in the joint name of the Pyongyang City Committee of the WPK and the Pyongyang City People's Committee and a wreath in the joint name of the Hyongjesan District Committee of the WPK and the Hyongjesan District People's Committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, wreaths were also laid before the martyrs cemetery of the CPV in Kaesong.

Chinese Embassy Lays Wreath before Friendship Tower
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 25 (KCNA) -- The Chinese embassy here laid a wreath before the Friendship Tower Tuesday on the occasion of the 55th anniversary of the entry of the Chinese People's Volunteers into the Korean front. 
 Amid the playing of the wreath-laying music, the participants placed a wreath before the tower in the name of the embassy and observed a moment's silence in memory of CPV martyrs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The embassy also laid a wreath before the martyrs cemetery of the CPV in Hyongjesan District, Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the Central Committee of the Association of the Chinese Residents in Korea laid wreaths respectively before the Friendship Tower and the martyrs cemetery of the CPV.
